The safe-local `vips` package keeps the original Debian source and binary
package names, but the build now has two layers:

1. Cargo builds the Rust `libvips.so.42` plus the deprecated ABI shims.
2. Meson builds the upstream C++ wrapper, tools, examples, docs, locales,
   manpages, GIR, and typelib artifacts against that staged ABI.

When updating the package, check both the Cargo dependency set and the Meson
feature/dependency surface. The safe-local upstream wrapper manifests under
`tests/upstream/` and the introspection smoke checker in
`scripts/check_introspection.sh` are part of the package contract.

 -- Jay Berkenbilt <qjb@debian.org>, Wed, 10 Sep 2014 08:26:55 -0400
